external_knowledge:
- "stars cruising in the vast ocean of social media" refers to influencers;
- "admirers" refers to followers;
- "cast over ten ripples (posts)" refers to influencers who have posted more than 10 pieces of content;
- "seas (categories)" refers to the categories in which the influencers belong;
- "size of their ripples" refers to the number of posts made by the influencers.

- Highly engaging: average engagement rate > 0.5;
- Significant following: follower count > 5000;
- Engagement prowess: determined by the average engagement rate in descending order.

sql:
SELECT name, average_engagement_rate
FROM influencers
WHERE name LIKE '%John%' AND follower_count > 10000;

SELECT name, follower_count
FROM influencers
ORDER BY follower_count DESC;
